BREAKTHROUGH: n_runs=1 counts are n-independent = A000255(f) + A000255(f+1)

n_runs=1 counts by free elements f:
  f=0: 1
  f=1: 4 = A000255(1) + A000255(2) = 1+3
  f=2: 14 = A000255(2) + A000255(3) = 3+11
  f=3: 64 = A000255(3) + A000255(4) = 11+53
  f=4: 362 = A000255(4) + A000255(5) = 53+309
  f=5: 2428 = A000255(5) + A000255(6) = 309+2119

These counts are THE SAME at n=5, n=6, n=7.

n_runs >= 2 counts DEPEND on n.
Example: (free=1, n_runs=2): 18, 36, 54 at n=5,6,7 (grows linearly)

IMPLICATION FOR THE PROOF:
The identity decomposes into single-run and multi-run parts.
The single-run part connects to A000255 via its recurrence.
The multi-run part involves n-dependent combinatorics.
